        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 9 at 4:00PM EDT by NWS Northern Indiana</headline>
        <description>At 400 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Berrien Springs, or 9 miles north of Buchanan, moving northeast at 50
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Berrien Springs, Eau Claire, Magician Lake, Dewey Lake, Indian Lake,
and Sandy Beach.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM EDT for
southwestern Michigan.</instruction>
